settings.description: The first level of Super Mario Land 2: 6 Golden Coins.

How to make your level goal look good:
Height should be 26, otherwise ending background will be one tile higher. Goal Roulette should be 8 tiles from right edge of the level and 5 tiles up from ground
Remake of the first level of a GameBoy game (enemy placements might not be accurate)

A remake of Super Mario World 1-1. Somehow, Rexes are now red and hopping. Banzai Bills are now smaller and homes in to you.
[Revision 2: Backtracking from room 2 disabled due to graphical glitches]

A remake of an unused level hidden in SMB3 NES/All-Stars SNES ROM.
I wanted to use Wrap Around but I gave up because many objects didn't go in intended positions.

Remake of the first Switch Palace in Super Mario World.
The Bonus Room Checkered Floors/Ceilings are glitched when they are longer than 15 tiles so I had to separate them with Unbreakable SMB1 Blocks.
A remake of Super Mario World 1-3. The rotating chain platforms aren't in SMB3, so several SMB1 Platforms have been added to help you collect coins.
A remake of Super Mario World 1-2. No Yoshi here, so Goomba Shoe is used instead.
